  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the broiler to high heat.",
    "Rinse the chicken thighs and pat them dry with paper towels.",
    "Mix together the olive oil, lemon juice, ghee, garlic powder, salt, black pepper, cumin, coriander, cayenne pepper, and Middle Eastern spice blend in a bowl.",
    "Add the chicken thighs to the bowl and toss to coat with the marinade.",
    "Thread the chicken thighs onto skewers, leaving a small space between each piece.",
    "Place the skewers on a broiler pan and broil for 10-12 minutes, or until cooked through.",
    "Serve the chicken hot, garnished with parsley, almonds, and a sprinkle of sumac.",
    "Garnish with lemon wedges and serve with pita bread, if desired.",
    "Let the chicken rest for 5 minutes before serving."
